column10:
Get organized and Stop the Noise with our classic Stonewash Aluminum KeyBar. Made of high-end aircraft-grade aluminum, and stonewashed for that rugged classic look. It's a simple yet sophisticated everyday carry sure to gain attention. Keep your essentials together in one perfect pocket sized package that can withstand some of the harshest environments.

What's included?

    • (1) Branded hinged tin
    • (1) KeyBar with a removable titanium pocket clip in the color of your choice
    • (2) custom designed stainless steel 1/2" screws (up to 4 keys)
    • (2) custom designed stainless steel 3/4" screws (up to 8 keys)
    • (2) custom designed stainless steel 7/8" screws (up to 12 keys)
    • (18) Washers
    • (2) O rings (allows you to adjust the tension)
    • (1) Titanium key fob link

    Will my keys fit?

    Use the following dimensions to find out:

    • Length of the KeyBar - 3.5"
    • Width of each rounded end - .95"
    • Distance between screw holes - 2.55"
    • Screw post diameter - .164"

How much does the KeyBar weigh?

    • Less than 2 ounces
    • Less than 4 house keys

    What can I put in the KeyBar?

    • Up to 12 keys and inserts with included screws
    • Up to 20 keys and inserts with extension screws

column9:
• Magnetic quick connect with rare-earth magnets
  • Small set available in Aluminum, Black Anodized Aluminum, Copper, or Brass
  • Medium set available in Aluminum
  • Includes 14mm titanium split rings
  • Add on colored split rings here
  • Use with your KeyBar for larger items like fobs
column10:
The Small and Medium MagNut set is a magnetic quick clasp specifically designed for the KeyBar but works on tools or other pesky items for which you need a quick mounting solution.

A set includes two MagNuts (a right and a left MagNut) each with a 1/2" titanium split ring (Medium MagNuts include stainless steel split rings).

MagNuts come in a choice of small, medium or large aluminum,  small brass or small copper MagNuts with pressed 1/4" x 1/4" rare-earth (Neodymium Iron Boron in Grade N52) magnetic cylinder insert, which has a pull force of 6 1/2 lbs. Medium aluminum MagNuts have a pull force of 18 lbs.

Note: These rare-earth magnets will lose their magnetic properties if heated above 175 degrees Fahrenheit (80 degrees Celcius). The strong magnetic fields of these rare-earth magnets can damage items such as television, computer monitors, credit cards, bank cards, computers, data carriers, video tapes, mechanical watches, hearing aids and loud speakers. Pace-makers may be damaged or switch to "Test-Mode" in the presence of a strong magnetic force, if a pace-maker or other bodily implant is in use, keep a minimum of 3 feet distance. Keep away from small children. Under no circumstances should you try to cut, saw or drill the rare earth magnet as the resulting dust is very flammable.  You should also not burn the magnet as it will create toxic fumes.

Brass and Copper MagNuts do aquire a patina and may not come as polished as shown in photos.

column10:
Want to keep it simple with a little flare? The Slayer Titanium KeyBar does just that. It's deeply carved pattern on both sides adds a rugged appeal and the satin finish of the natural titanium doesn't overdo it. It's truly a crowd pleaser. Likewise, the carved finish allows for a "quick check" when doing that every day carry pat down to make sure you have all your essentials with you. Plus, it's made of 100% titanium so you know it's durable and long lasting.

What's included?

      • (1) Branded hinged tin
      • (1) KeyBar with a removable titanium pocket clip
      • Comes with Custom SS Screws
      • (2) custom designed stainless steel 1/2" screws (up to 4 keys)
      • (2) custom designed stainless steel 3/4" screws (up to 8 keys)
      • (2) custom designed stainless steel 7/8" screws (up to 12 keys)
      • (18) Washers
      • (2) O rings (allows you to adjust the tension)
      • (1) Titanium key fob link

    Will my keys fit?

    Use the following dimensions to find out:
      • Length of the KeyBar - 3.5"
      • Width of each rounded end - .95"
      • Distance between screw holes - 2.55"
      • Screw post diameter - .164"

How much does the KeyBar weigh?

      • Less than 2 ounces
      • Less than 4 house keys

    What can I put in the KeyBar?

      • Up to 12 keys and inserts with included screws
      • Up to 28 keys and inserts with extension screws

column9: Be prepared for anything with our MUT which features a titanium body and an easy to install or remove steel razor blade. Includes spare blades which can be installed without disassembling your KeyBar.
column10:
Utility tool with titanium body and steel blade. Tool includes ten replacement blades. Replacement mini utility blades are available at Harbor Freight. Blade can be removed without having to disassemble your KeyBar.

<u>Blade Housing Installation Instructions</u>

First install a washer.  Then, take the thumb stud plate and install it with the screw heads down.  Next, place the tension plate on top of the thumb stud plate.  Finish assembling KeyBar.

<u>Blade Installation Instructions</u>

To install the blade, open the tension plate all the way to expose the pocket.  Drop the razor blade into place, making sure it is flat in the pocket so that it is secure.  Close tension plate. Mini Utility Tool Insert is ready for use.

<u>Disclaimer:</u>

The KeyBar Mini Utility Tool Insert is intended for use with your KeyBar product.  The Mini Utility Tool Insert is, of course, very sharp and could cause bodily injury if not handled carefully.  Users of the KeyBar Mini Utility Tool Insert should take special care to ensure that the blade insert itself is not left exposed when not in use, and that it is folded fully into the closed position.  Never use the Mini Utility Tool Insert while otherwise occupied or distracted, such as when operating a motor vehicle.  Users of the Mini Utility Tool Insert should also use extreme caution when using the Mini Utility Tool Insert, as there is the potential for bodily injury.   The Mini Utility Tool Insert is not a toy, and is likewise not intended to be used as a hunting, or similar knife, and will not withstand forces necessary to cut through thick or solid materials.  The Mini Utility Tool Insert is not a replacement for ordinary, or everyday knives, but is only intended for very light use.  KeyBar, LLC is not responsible for any injury caused by misuse of the Mini Utility Tool Insert or negligence on the part of its owner or user.

column9: Configure your custom keybar below, then purchase the $25 deposit. After we receive your deposit order, we will send a PDF proof of your custom keybar design along with an invoice for the balance.
column10:
Custom KeyBar Process:

  • Customer fills out request form and receives an estimated price.
  • Customer adds $25 deposit to cart and completes checkout.
  • Art and options are reviewed by customs department for compatibility.
  • Proof and adjusted quote or compatibility issues are sent via email. Requests are processed in the order they are received.
  • Customer approves or requests changes to design and lists any accessories to be added to invoice.
  • Once the design is approved we will send a final invoice.
  • Once balance payment is received, your custom KeyBar typically ships within 7 business days.

General Information/Limitations:

  • Custom requests, artwork, and related emails are responded to as soon as possible.
  • Quotes and invoices are valid for 2 weeks from date sent.
  • Refunds or exchanges are not applicable for custom orders.
  • Carbon Fiber cannot be customized and Carbon Fiber fronts will feature the KeyBar logo. Carbon Fiber backs can only be paired with Carbon Fiber fronts.
  • Image requirements:
    • Ideal image is single layer, black and white vector, or high-resolution computer created/clipart style images. (View ideal samples here)
    • Screen shots, grayscale, heavily distressed images, drawings, pictures, copyright stamped or watermarked images will not be accepted.
  • Must not be a trademark or copyright of an organization from whom you have not acquired permission. By submitting a request, you certify that you have permission to use the images you provide.
  • We retain the right to duplicate a custom KeyBar® unless the customer is the holder of a trademark or copyright used in the design.
  • We offer discounts on multiple units for promotional purposes, gifts, or resale. If you are interested, please list the quantity in the additional comments on the request.
  • If you are interested in a 1 of 1 custom design, please let us know.
  • For customization questions, email info@keybar.us.

column9:

column10:
Get organized with the revolver inspired aluminum rotating pen (or anything else!) holder. Made in the USA.

KeyBar's Quick Draw revolving desk organizer helps you show off/organize your desk tools in style. Can be used as a pen holder, tool holder, art supplies holder, etc.

The spinning action is achieved using high-end skateboard ball bearings allowing for a smooth and long-lasting action. With 8 different slots, you can store a vast assortment of pens and tools that you need at the ready. Together this makes the Quick Draw an amazing desk organization display, conversation piece, and fidget-spinner for those moments at your desk that you just need to spin some more ideas into your thought process.

  • Made from a 3 inch 6061 billet aluminum block 
  • 8 Pen holes measuring  - .625 inch in diameter
  • 4 inch overall height
  • Total weight: 23.25oz

column10: The Keyrabiner 4.0 is here - and it's more durable than ever! When creating the 4.0 model, we wanted to enhance the thin, lightweight features of the 3.0 Keyrabiner; however, we really wanted to apply some of the durable and easy-to-use features we loved about the classic 2.0 Keyrabiner.\n\nBy upgrading the fundamentals of what we and our community love about this insert, we're able to create the best Keyrabiner yet! Each individual Keyrabiner is made of pure titanium. The functionality is designed to act like a carabiner and can fold into the KeyBar for convenient storage. To ensure complete quality control, each Keyrabiner is crafted with our water jet right here in the USA.

column9: The enhanced deep carry comes in titanium and can fit any KeyBar that features the cutout slot for our regular clip. The clip will not work with KeyBars that have milled clips that screw onto the KeyBar. The clip features a thicker body, providing more durability and stability in your pocket.
column10:
We have designed an enhanced, deep carry clip to fit any KeyBar that features the cutout slot for our regular clip. The clip will not work with KeyBars that have milled clips that screw onto the KeyBar. These clips are made out of grade 5 titanium and are cut in-house with our water jet. Features of the enhanced design include a thicker and more durable structure. The clips also feature a smooth, surface finish.

The bottom end of the clip is a lot thicker to provide more stability in your pocket. When connecting the clip to the back plate of the KeyBar, we replaced the traditional circular cutout with a square cutout to allow the screw to connect easier for an easier assembly.

column10:
Nose art is a decorative painting or design on the fuselage of an aircraft, usually on the front fuselage. While begun for practical reasons of identifying friendly units, the practice evolved to express the individuality often constrained by the uniformity of the military, to evoke memories of home and peacetime life. Thus, we give a nod to those dog fighters of WW2 with the Titanium Stealth Bomber KeyBar featuring the most iconic of nose arts, the shark bomber. Made of 100% titanium and laser engraved.

column10:
Machined from 6061 Billet Aluminum, the KeyBar Mallets have been a show-stopper everywhere we bring them. With it's distinctive look and feel of wielding Mjölnir itself, it's only fitting that we decorate these Mallets with Nordic themed graphics. The Stonewashed and Darkened variations both sport Rune engravings down the handles where as the fully engraved version applies that same theme to the Mallet head itself. With a total weight of 2lbs, they are lightweight but durable enough to withstand a serious beating.

We've used one of these around the shop for years on things we didn't want to damage or mar using a standard hammer. Good for smashing stuff too!

column9:
• Limited run - only 5 available
  • Magnetic closure keeps wallet secure
  • Laser Engraved Beskar pattern with Imperial and MudHorn insignia
  • Handmade with top quality hand-picked materials
column10:
This aluminum wallet, we dubbed the "Card Catcher", was designed and produced in-house using the best quality material that were hand-picked specifically for this product. The outside features a laser engraved Beskar pattern with the Imperial insignia adorning one side, and the MudHorn insignia on the flip. The two halves are connected with a piece of brown leather and heat treated screws for classy yet rugged contrast. The Card Catcher stays securely closed using rare earth magnets, as found in our popular MagNuts.

These are completely hand assembled, and hand polished in-house.

column10:
Looking for the ultimate finishing touch on your custom bumpers? The Redeemer Shackle is KeyBar’s newest addition to the KeyBar brand. This truck shackle is serious. And by serious, we mean SERIOUS. With a max load capacity of 20,000lbs (10 tons) and a breaking point of a massive 47,000lbs. Styled with a unique angular cut that’s sure to draw attention they just beg to be noticed. Made out of a solid block of billet 6061 aircraft-grade aluminum. Made 100% in the USA. The Matte Black is cerakoted and topped off with a custom laser engraved KeyBar logo. Both sets come with a set of Grade-5 3/4" Bolts nuts with deviated threads.


What's included?

    • (2)"The Redeemer" Shackles in Machined or Black finish
    • (2) Shackle Bolts
    • (2)Heavy-Duty threaded nuts

    • Total Weight: 4.5lbs (2 shackles, 2 nuts, 2 bolts)
    • Dimensions per shackle: 5” x 4.5” 2”
    • Price is for set of 2
    • Load Test: 20,000lbs
    • Test Failure: 48,000lbs
    • Testing done by ACUREN Materials Engineering & Testing

column10: Trying to simplify your KeyBar to it's max potential? The Titanium Multi-Tool Insert is KeyBar's all-in-one insert for KeyBar and KeyBar JRs. This insert has so many functionalities, its insane to think about just how we managed to fit them all into such a small package. The tool has a chamfered end to be used as a prybar, followed by a bottle opener cut out and a ridge indented finger rest for added torque when using the aforementioned functions. That ridge line also doubles as a cap-grip opener when seated and closed into the KeyBar. On the flip side there's a laser engraved ruler with 1/16" increments for those times you need to take small measurements without having to whip out a flimsy tape measurer. Even more?? The thumbstud switch also acts as a small nail file, and yet again, KeyBar logo side has the same cuts to be utilized as a forever-strike!

column10:
Designed by aerospace engineer Cory Duncan, who was tired of the traditional folding leather wallet that is too bulky and reminiscent of the billfolds and wallets from his grandfather's generation.

Using space age materials like titanium and design concepts found on fighter jets and formula one race cars, Cory created a line of mechanical wallets that are sleek, streamlined, efficient, modular  and incredibly impressive.

Each wallet has hours on hours of machine and assembly time to complete one. We use the best equipment available to manufacture and quality will ALWAYS come before quantity. Each wallet is anodized and finished by hand giving each its own characteristics, making no two the same. Like a fine time piece they are designed to last and be something that could be passed to down to the next generation. Like the old saying goes "you get what you pay for" and that holds true here.

Note: These include rare-earth magnets will lose their magnetic properties if heated above 175 degrees Fahrenheit (80 degrees Celcius). The strong magnetic fields of these rare-earth magnets can damage items such as television, computer monitors, credit cards, bank cards, computers, data carriers, video tapes, mechanical watches, hearing aids and loud speakers. Pace-makers may be damaged or switch to “Test-Mode” in the presence of a strong magnetic force, if a pace-maker or other bodily implant is in use, keep a minimum of 3 feet distance. Keep away from small children. Under no circumstances should you try to cut, saw or drill the rare earth magnet as the resulting dust is very flammable.  You should also not burn the magnet as it will create toxic fumes.

This KeyBar tool insert bundle includes 2 of our most popular inserts! Lightweight and light duty Grade 5 titanium phillips head screwdriver tool featuring a stop pin. The Titanium Whachamacallit Tool Insert is KeyBar’s all-in-one insert for KeyBar and KeyBar JRs. This insert has so many functionalities, its insane to think about just how we managed to fit them all into such a small package. The tool has a chamfered end to be used as a prybar, followed by a bottle opener cut out and a ridge indented finger rest for added torque when using the aforementioned functions. That ridge line also doubles as a cap-grip opener when seated and closed into the KeyBar. On the flip side there’s a laser engraved ruler with 1/16″ increments for those times you need to take small measurements without having to whip out a flimsy tape measurer. Even more?? The thumbstud switch also acts as a small nail file, and yet again, KeyBar logo side has the same cuts to be utilized as a forever-strike!

column5: Insert Bundle: Mini Utility Tool & Phillips/Flat Head Screwdrivers
column10:
This KeyBar tool insert bundle includes 2 of our most popular inserts! Lightweight and light duty Grade 5 titanium flathead and phillips head screwdriver tools, each with stop pin. Utility tool with titanium body and steel blade. Tool includes ten replacement blades. Replacement mini utility blades are available at Harbor Freight. Blade can be removed without having to disassemble your KeyBar.

Blade Housing Installation Instructions

First install a washer. Then, take the thumb stud plate and install it with the screw heads down. Next, place the tension plate on top of the thumb stud plate. Finish assembling KeyBar.

Blade Installation Instructions

To install the blade, open the tension plate all the way to expose the pocket. Drop the razor blade into place, making sure it is flat in the pocket so that it is secure. Close tension plate. Mini Utility Tool Insert is ready for use.

Disclaimer:

The KeyBar Mini Utility Tool Insert is intended for use with your KeyBar product. The Mini Utility Tool Insert is, of course, very sharp and could cause bodily injury if not handled carefully. Users of the KeyBar Mini Utility Tool Insert should take special care to ensure that the blade insert itself is not left exposed when not in use, and that it is folded fully into the closed position. Never use the Mini Utility Tool Insert while otherwise occupied or distracted, such as when operating a motor vehicle. Users of the Mini Utility Tool Insert should also use extreme caution when using the Mini Utility Tool Insert, as there is the potential for bodily injury. The Mini Utility Tool Insert is not a toy, and is likewise not intended to be used as a hunting, or similar knife, and will not withstand forces necessary to cut through thick or solid materials. The Mini Utility Tool Insert is not a replacement for ordinary, or everyday knives, but is only intended for very light use. KeyBar, LLC is not responsible for any injury caused by misuse of the Mini Utility Tool Insert or negligence on the part of its owner or user.

What's included?

      • (1) Stonewashed Titanium Phillips Head Screwdriver Insert
      • (1) Stonewashed Titanium Flathead/Pry Tool Screwdriver Insert
      • (1) Stonewashed Titanium Mini Utility Tool Insert
      • (5) Blade replacements

column10:
Sometimes, you have a very important document come in the mail and just ripping it open or using a pocket knife may lead to a disastrous end with cutting through the contents of the envelope. So, we have developed our very own titanium Letter Opener insert for KeyBar dubbed "The Noah". Hand ground on both sides allows for an easy tear and smooth glide while opening up any envelope. Easily accessed by a fleur de lis styled thumb tab that's been rounded off to ensure no snares in your pocket as well as for a quick and smooth release acton. The insert is indented just before the opener to allow for a tighter grip between the index finger and thumb.

Available in 3 different color options: Polished Titanium, Anodized Bronze, and Radiant Teal

NOTE: Radiant teal is an iridescent color that fluctuates between light blue and purple in the right light.

column10:
The Hatchback minimalist wallet has the Vicehardware signature style written all over it. It features a machine milled, aluminum body with accompanying custom-made laser engravings on the front and back plates. It's a smart and simple design which acts as a perfect, lightweight, simple, and minimalistic card holder.

Designed by aerospace engineer Cory Duncan, who was tired of the traditional folding leather wallet that is too bulky and reminiscent of the billfolds and wallets from his grandfather's generation.

Using space age materials like titanium and design concepts found on fighter jets and formula one race cars, Cory created a line of mechanical wallets that are sleek, streamlined, efficient, modular  and incredibly impressive.

Each wallet has hours on hours of machine and assembly time to complete one. We use the best equipment available to manufacture and quality will ALWAYS come before quantity. Each wallet is anodized and finished by hand giving each its own characteristics, making no two the same. Like a fine time piece they are designed to last and be something that could be passed to down to the next generation. Like the old saying goes "you get what you pay for" and that holds true here.

The limited edition Battleworn Cerakote Aluminum KeyVice Carabiner features a very unique cerakote finish done by C and B Quality Coatings. Fluorescent orange stripes complimenting a turquoise blue base and battleworn black scuff marks give this KeyBar a steam punk feel to it. column10:
These very special Quick Draw pen holders have a top machined from a solid piece of Bocote Wood and a bottom machined from a solid piece of billet brass. The wooden portion has been painstakingly hand sanded, oiled, and lacquered for a surreal smooth and semi-glossy finish. Each bottom piece of brass has been hand sand blasted and then polished to add to the rustic and timeless look of these incredible pen holders. 

Bocote is an exotic wood native to Mexico, Central America, and the West Indies. It features a wide range of grain patterns from straight to wild, with curved lines and swirls. The color ranges from golden brown to tan to golden yellow. It is a hard, heavy, and dense wood, strong and stiff, with a medium texture.

Get organized with the revolver inspired aluminum rotating pen (or anything else!) holder. Made in the USA.

Looking for the ultimate finishing touch on your custom bumpers? The Redeemer Shackle is KeyBar’s newest addition to the KeyBar brand. This truck shackle is serious. And by serious, we mean SERIOUS. With a max load capacity of 20,000lbs (10 tons) and a breaking point of a massive 47,000lbs. Styled with a unique angular cut that’s sure to draw attention they just beg to be noticed. Made out of a solid block of billet 6061 aircraft-grade aluminum. Made 100% in the USA. The Matte Black is cerakoted and topped off with a custom laser engraved KeyBar logo. Both sets come with a set of Grade-5 3/4" Bolts nuts with deviated threads.

What's included?

    • (2)"The Redeemer" Shackles in Machined or Black finish
    • (2) Shackle Bolts
    • (2)Heavy-Duty threaded nuts
    Specs
    • Total Weight: 4.5lbs (2 shackles, 2 nuts, 2 bolts)
    • Dimensions per shackle: 5” x 4.5” 2”
    • Price is for set of 2
    • Load Test: 20,000lbs
    • Test Failure: 48,000lbs
    • Testing done by ACUREN Materials Engineering & Testing

column10:
The Westerner Aluminum shows off some of our best laser skills in terms of detail work. Deep laser engraved and then hand polished, the front depicts a Victorian engraved six shooter with the barrel pointed right at one KeyBar screw whole. The back side shows a desert scene with an ornate paisley style sun, a lone ranger cowboy and trusty steed overlooking the vast western plane. Stay organized and keep it together cowboy.

What's included?

      • (1) Branded hinged tin
      • (1) KeyBar with a removable titanium pocket clip in the color of your choice
      • Comes with heat treated Stainless Steel Screws
      • (2) 1/2" screws (up to 4 keys)
      • (2) 3/4" screws (up to 8 keys)
      • (2) 7/8" screws (up to 12 keys)
      • (18) Washers
      • (2) O rings (allows you to adjust the tension)
      • (1) Titanium key fob link

How much does the KeyBar weigh?

      • Less than 2 ounces
      • Less than 4 house keys

    What can I put in the KeyBar?

      • Up to 12 keys and inserts with included screws
      • Up to 28 keys and inserts with extension screws

column10:
Show off your fighting and free spirit with the OD Green G10 Bomber KeyBar. Made of extremely durable and lightweight G10 colored in OD Green,  these KeyBar bombers feature a WW2 nose art graphic inspired by the famous Warhawk aircraft. Exhaust vents, USAF emblem and that classic Warhawk bomber face make this a standout KeyBar you for sure don't want to miss.

What's included?

column9:
• Vintage Westinghouse Butterscotch Micarta front
  • 2-Tone Sandblasted Titanium Back
  • Polished Titanium Milled Pocket Clip
column10:
A KeyBar that is truly vintage in both it's appearance and make-up. The front faceplate is crafted from authentic Westinghouse Micarta in a butterscotch coloration. Compared to the rest of the KeyBars we make, this front faceplate is quite thick, and that's because we wanted to keep the true authenticity of this classic material in tact without too much modification. After it's CNC cut it is then sanded, washed in a hypersonic bath, and finally lightly polished. The back is a 2 tone sandblasted/polished bronze titanium with the newly revamped milled titanium pocket clip (a throwback to classic KeyBars bringing it to our modern understanding and techniques). The clip is polished and sanded helping to bring the classic 2 tone appearance of this KeyBar all together. The result is something breathtaking. An ode to the craftsmen of yesterday, the one's who poured their heart and soul into their work making everything by hand before machine technology was as abundant as it is today.

What's included?

      • (1) Branded hinged tin
      • (1) Authentic Westinghouse Butterscotch Micarta/Titanium KeyBar
      • (1) Titanium milled pocket clip
      • Comes with Stainless Steel Screws
      • (2) 1/2" screws (up to 4 keys)
      • (2) 3/4" screws (up to 8 keys)
      • (2) 7/8" screws (up to 12 keys)
      • (18) Washers
      • (2) O rings (allows you to adjust the tension)
      • (1) Titanium key fob link

column10:
One of our favorite past times, and the best reason to keep a key organizer/multitool on hand, is fishing! Being located on the coast of southern Georgia, we know fishing. It's in our blood and some of the best memories we have are made though our fishing experiences. So with these KeyBars, we wanted to share that love of fishing with you and hopefully rekindle some good memories and "the one that got away" stories. We chose 3 of the most popular fish across the USA, the Largemouth Bass, Rainbow Trout, and Red Drum (aka Redfish and Spot Tail Bass). These KeyBars also go through a series of processes in order to make the skin "shimmer" like that of real fish skin.

Forged in the healm of the KeyBar workshop, the Dracarys KeyBar commemorates the launch of one of our most favorite Sunday night specials. The front face plate is from a solid piece of Carbon Fiber. The back is deep engraved aluminum featuring a prominent dragon's eye and the phrase "NOT TODAY" down the pocket clip side. It is then polished to deliver a striking contrast. If your a fan, like we are, then this is a KeyBar you sure don't want to miss out on. Keep a piece of Westeros in your pockets daily.

What's included?

      • (1) Branded hinged tin
      • (1) KeyBar with a titanium pocket clip included
      • Comes with Heat Treated Stainless Steel Screws
      • (2) 1/2" screws (up to 4 keys)
      • (2) 3/4" screws (up to 8 keys)
      • (2) 7/8" screws (up to 12 keys)
      • (18) Washers
      • (2) O rings (allows you to adjust the tension)
      • (1) Titanium key fob link

    Will my keys fit?

    Use the following dimensions to find out:

      • Length of the KeyBar - 3.5"
      • Width of each rounded end - .95"
      • Distance between screw holes - 2.55"
      • Screw post diameter - .164"

How much does the KeyBar weigh?

      • Less than 2 ounces
      • Less than 4 house keys

    What can I put in the KeyBar?

      • Up to 12 keys and inserts with included screws
      • Up to 28 keys and inserts with extension screws

Utility Tool | Pick | Quick Key Tab | + More

The Mini Utility tool with titanium body and steel blades. Tool includes ten replacement blades. Replacement mini utility blades are available at Harbor Freight. Blade can be removed without having to disassemble your KeyBar.

Blade Installation Instructions

To install the blade, open the tension plate all the way to expose the pocket.  Drop the razor blade into place, making sure it is flat in the pocket so that it is secure.  Close tension plate. Mini Utility Tool Insert is ready for use.

Disclaimer:

The KeyBar Mini Utility Tool Insert is intended for use with your KeyBar product.  The Mini Utility Tool Insert is, of course, very sharp and could cause bodily injury if not handled carefully.  Users of the KeyBar Mini Utility Tool Insert should take special care to ensure that the blade insert itself is not left exposed when not in use, and that it is folded fully into the closed position.  Never use the Mini Utility Tool Insert while otherwise occupied or distracted, such as when operating a motor vehicle.  Users of the Mini Utility Tool Insert should also use extreme caution when using the Mini Utility Tool Insert, as there is the potential for bodily injury.   The Mini Utility Tool Insert is not a toy, and is likewise not intended to be used as a hunting, or similar knife, and will not withstand forces necessary to cut through thick or solid materials.  The Mini Utility Tool Insert is not a replacement for ordinary, or everyday knives, but is only intended for very light use.  KeyBar, LLC is not responsible for any injury caused by misuse of the Mini Utility Tool Insert or negligence on the part of its owner or user.

column10:
Made from solid titanium, the Flathead Screwdriver Tool Insert 2.0 is a lightweight and light duty Grade 5 titanium #2 flat head screwdriver that locks in the open and closed position thanks to our new titanium KB Detent Lock system. Can also function as a pry tool.

The KB Detent Lock uses torsion bars with stainless steel studs that jump over cams machined on the tool inserts giving a satisfying SNAP when opened and closed with just the right amount of resistance.

The locks are stackable allowing you to add extra tools.

The Full Size KeyBar takes TWO of the new Tools Per Lock ; the JR Size only uses ONE tool per lock

For a full size KeyBar, you'll receive the FlatheadScrewdriver Tool Insert 2.0, the second tool insert you select below, plus the full size lock. For the JR size KeyBar

Phillips Head Screwdriver 2.0: Titanium #2 Phillips Head Screwdriver.

Can Opener: Titanium CNC Machined Can Opener designed for the survivalist.

Mini Chisel: S35VN Steel solid version of MUT.

column10:
A wolf howling at the full moon. To some a creepy scene, to others serenity. The Wolf's Delight Titanium KeyBar has a deep engraved and multicolored picturesque scene of a wolf howling at the full moon with a traditional creepy forest landscape. The back side is treated the same but with a close up wolf howling at the moon graphic. The entire KeyBar is deep laser engraved titanium that is then laser polished, paint brushed anodized, and hand sanded for a breathtaking contrast appearance of the material. Comes with a multicolored Deep Carry 2.0 pocket clip and heat colored stainless steel screws.

What's included?

      • (1) Branded hinged tin
      • (1) Custom KeyBar with a titanium pocket clip
      • (2) custom designed stainless steel 1/2" screws (up to 4 keys)
      • (2) custom designed stainless steel 3/4" screws (up to 8 keys)
      • (2) custom designed stainless steel 7/8" screws (up to 12 keys)
      • (18) Washers
      • (2) O rings (allows you to adjust the tension)
      • (1) Titanium key fob link

    Will my keys fit?

    Use the following dimensions to find out:

      • Length of the KeyBar - 3.5"
      • Width of each rounded end - .95"
      • Distance between screw holes - 2.55"
      • Screw post diameter - .164"

How much does the KeyBar weigh?

      • Less than 2 ounces
      • Less than 4 house keys

    What can I put in the KeyBar?

      • Up to 12 keys and inserts with included screws
      • Up to 28 keys and inserts with extension screws

column9:
Our 6 newly updated tool inserts are designed to work with our new Titanium KB Detent Lock allowing the tool to snap into the open/closed position with just the right amount of resistance.

  • Made of S35VN Steel .085" Thick (cannot be colored)
  • Cam Lock uses torsion bars with stainless steel studs
  • Locks are stackable allowing you to add extra tools
  • The Full Size KeyBar takes TWO of the new Tools Per Lock
  • KeyBar JR uses ONE tool per lock
  • Full size KeyBar: Receives the Mini Chisel Tool Insert 2.0, full size lock and second tool from dropdown
  • KeyBar JR: Receive the Mini Chisel Tool Insert 2.0 plus the JR size lock
column10:
Made from MagnaCut Steel, the new Mini Chisel Tool Insert is the next level version of the Mini Utility Tool Insert.

The KB Detent Lock uses torsion bars with stainless steel studs that jump over cams machined on the tool inserts giving a satisfying SNAP when opened and closed with just the right amount of resistance.

The locks are stackable allowing you to add extra tools.

The Full Size KeyBar takes TWO of the new Tools Per Lock ; the JR Size only uses ONE tool per lock

For a full size KeyBar, you’ll receive the Mini Chisel Tool Insert 2.0, the second tool insert you select below, plus the full size lock. For the JR size KeyBar, you’ll receive the Mini Chisel Tool Insert 2.0 plus the JR size lock.

Disclaimer:

The KeyBar Chisel Tool Insert is intended for use with your KeyBar product.  The Chisel Tool Insert is, of course, very sharp and could cause bodily injury if not handled carefully.  Users of the KeyBar Chisel Tool Insert should take special care to ensure that the blade insert itself is not left exposed when not in use, and that it is folded fully into the closed position.  Never use the Chisel Tool Insert while otherwise occupied or distracted, such as when operating a motor vehicle.  Users of the Chisel Tool Insert should also use extreme caution when using the Chisel Tool Insert, as there is the potential for bodily injury.

The Chisel Tool Insert is not a toy, and is likewise not intended to be used as a hunting, or similar knife, and will not withstand forces necessary to cut through thick or solid materials.  The Chisel Tool Insert is not a replacement for ordinary, or everyday knives, but is only intended for very light use.  KeyBar, LLC is not responsible for any injury caused by misuse of the Chisel Tool Insert or negligence on the part of its owner or user.

Secondary Tool Options for Full Size KeyBar KB Detent Lock System

Mini Utility Tool 2.0 : Box cutter tool with titanium body and steel blade.

Bottle Bomber 2.0: Titanium Bottle opener features a quick access tab, flathead screwdriver, and a pry tool.

Flat head Screwdriver 2.0: Titanium #2 Flat Head Screwdriver. Can also function as a pry tool.

Phillips Head Screwdriver 2.0: Titanium #2 Phillips Head Screwdriver.

Can Opener: Titanium CNC Machined Can Opener designed for the survivalist.

column5: St. Pat's Bundle: KeyVice Titanium Carabiner + Slayer Titanium KeyBar + Small Brass MagNuts
column9:
• St. Pat's Special
  • KeyVice Carabiner and Slayer KeyBar feature bronze and green highlighting
  • KeyBar includes bronze 2.0 deep carry titanium pocket clip
  • Free Brass MagNuts
  • Add Custom Vice Hardware F22 Titanium Wallet!
column10:
We are offering a triple deal that includes a KeyVice Billet Titanium Carabiner, Slayer Titaniu KeyBar and small Brass MagNuts at a special price! The Carabiner and Slayer KeyBar feature bronze and green anodizing. PLUS, add the Vice Hardware F22 Titanium Wallet, customized to match the bundle and get 20% off the wallet! Grab this St. Pat's Bundle while you can - supplies are limited!

What's included?

    • (1) Bronze and Green KeyVice Billet Titanium Carabiner (2.75" x 0.25") that is large enough to fit any key fobs and accessories you need to keep together. The titanium gate was designed to prevent any accidental slip to the side so you know your belongings are secure. The bottom hole is perfect for attaching a set of MagNuts to hang a KeyBar off of, further expanding your minimal carry in a quick and easy to access organized package. 
    • (1) Bronze and Green Anodized Slayer Titanium KeyBar in a branded hinged tin with a bronze 2.0 titanium deep carry pocket clip, (2) 1/2" screws (up to 4 keys), (2) 3/4" screws (up to 8 keys, (2) 7/8" screws (up to 12 keys), (18) Washers, (2) O rings (allows you to adjust the tension), (1) Titanium key fob link
    • (1) Small Brass MagNut Set with pressed 1/4″ x 1/4″ rare-earth (Neodymium Iron Boron in Grade N52) magnetic cylinder insert, which has a pull force of 6 1/2 lbs. Note: These rare-earth magnets will lose their magnetic properties if heated above 175 degrees Fahrenheit (80 degrees Celcius). The strong magnetic fields of these rare-earth magnets can damage items such as television, computer monitors, credit cards, bank cards, computers, data carriers, video tapes, mechanical watches, hearing aids and loud speakers. Pace-makers may be damaged or switch to “Test-Mode” in the presence of a strong magnetic force, if a pace-maker or other bodily implant is in use, keep a minimum of 3 feet distance. Keep away from small children. Under no circumstances should you try to cut, saw or drill the rare earth magnet as the resulting dust is very flammable. You should also not burn the magnet as it will create toxic fumes.

    Will my keys fit?

    Use the following dimensions to find out:

    • Length of the KeyBar - 3.5" (Full size) or 3.0625" (JR)
    • Width of each rounded end - .95"
    • Distance between screw holes - 2.55" (Full Size) or 2.25" (JR)
    • Screw post diameter - .164"

How much does the KeyBar weigh?

    • Less than 2 ounces
    • Less than 4 house keys

    What can I put in the KeyBar?

    • 4-5 keys and inserts with included screws (JR)
    • Up to 12 keys and inserts with included screws (Full Size)
    • Up to 28 keys and inserts with extension screws (Both Sizes)

  • Arrives in Blister Packaging
  • Perfect Small but Useful Pocket Tool
  • Great Gift

column10:
Get organized and Stop the Noise with our classic Stonewashed Aluminum KeyBar JR. Made of high-end aircraft-grade aluminum, and stonewashed for that rugged classic look. It's a minimal yet sophisticated everyday carry sure to help you keep your essentials together in one perfect pocket sized package that can withstand some of the harshest environments. We've paired it with some of our most popular tool inserts: MagNut, Multi-Tool, Pick and Tweezers. The aluminum MagNut is a magnetic quick release specifically designed for the KeyBar to allow quick and easy connection for larger items, like your key fob, to your KeyBar. With a pull force of 6 1/2 lbs., items attached to your KeyBar with the MagNut are secure. The titanium Multi-Tool Insert has a chamfered end to be used as a prybar, followed by a bottle opener cut out and a ridge indented finger rest for added torque when using the aforementioned functions. That ridge line also doubles as a cap-grip opener when seated and closed into the KeyBar. On the flip side there's a laser engraved ruler with 1/16" increments for those times you need to take small measurements quickly. The thumbstud switch also acts as a small nail file, and finally, the logo side has the same cuts to be utilized as a forever-strike. Both the pick and tweezers are also made out of titanium.

What's included?

    • (1) Stonewashed Aluminum KeyBar JR (Blister Packaged)
    • (1) Small Aluminum MagNut Quick Release Set
    • (1) Titanium Multi-Tool Insert
    • (1) Titanium Pick Insert
    • (1) Titanium Tweezers Insert

    Specs

    • Length of the KeyBar - 3.0625"
    • Width of rounded end - .95"
    • Distance between screw holes - 2.25"
    • Screw post diameter - .164"
    • Weight - XXXXXXX

Additional Information

    • The small MagNut set includes two MagNuts (a right and a left MagNut) each with a 1/2" diameter split ring and is pressed with 1/4" x 1/4" rare-earth (Neodymium Iron Boron in Grade N52) magnetic cylinder insert, which has a pull force of 6 1/2 lbs. Note: These rare-earth magnets will lose their magnetic properties if heated above 175 degrees Fahrenheit (80 degrees Celcius). The strong magnetic fields of these rare-earth magnets can damage items such as television, computer monitors, credit cards, bank cards, computers, data carriers, video tapes, mechanical watches, hearing aids and loud speakers. Pace-makers may be damaged or switch to "Test-Mode" in the presence of a strong magnetic force, if a pace-maker or other bodily implant is in use, keep a minimum of 3 feet distance. Keep away from small children. Under no circumstances should you try to cut, saw or drill the rare earth magnet as the resulting dust is very flammable.  You should also not burn the magnet as it will create toxic fumes.

  • Green, Aqua or Orange Embrite™ front paired with a different material clip side
  • Additional information can be found below
column10:
We've taken Embrite™, a phosphorescent composite material manufactured by TEC Accessories, and created these Limited Edition KeyBar models! This proprietary cutting edge glow technology is used to create a material that will glow for hours when exposed to sunlight or UV light. The longer the exposure time and the higher the light intensity, the longer and brighter it will glow. Depending upon the color, glow times can last over 12 hours! We're offering three Embrite™ color options for the front: Green, Aqua and Orange. The Green is paired with a Bronze Stonewashed Titanium clip side, the Aqua is paired with a Blue Stonewashed Titanium clip side, and the Orange is paired with a Green Micarta Clip Side. A Standard Titanium Pocket Clip is included, with the added ability to upgrade to a colored clip, including Light Green as a color choice. Additional information about the Embrite™ colors we've selected is below.
Color Daylight Color Glow Color  Glow Duration
Green Pale Green Green 12+ Hours
Aqua White Aqua 12+ Hours
Orange Bright Orange Orange-Gold 6-8 Hours

column10:

column9:
• Limited Edition Green Embrite™/Titanium KeyBar
  • Features zombie hand design created by @colorfulfilth
  • Green front can glow for 12+ hours
  • Includes bronze/purple titanium deep carry pocket clip
  • Additional information can be found below
column10:
We've taken Embrite™, a phosphorescent composite material manufactured by TEC Accessories, and created these Limited Edition KeyBar models! This proprietary cutting edge glow technology is used to create a material that will glow for hours when exposed to sunlight or UV light. The longer the exposure time and the higher the light intensity, the longer and brighter it will glow. Depending upon the color, glow times can last over 12 hours! This limited edition version includes a green Embrite™ front featuring a zombie hand design that has been both laser engraved and UV printed. The clip side is anodized green and features a similar zombie hand design that has also been laser engraved and UV Printed. The clip we've selected for this KeyBar is a stonewashed titanium Deep Carry 2.0 anodized in bronze/purple. The front can glow for 12+ hours. We partnered with @colorfulfilth to create this awesome design.

What's included?

      • (1) Branded hinged tin
      • (1) KeyBar with a deep carry titanium pocket clip
      • (2) custom designed stainless steel 1/2" screws (up to 4 keys)
      • (2) custom designed stainless steel 3/4" screws (up to 8 keys)
      • (2) custom designed stainless steel 7/8" screws (up to 12 keys)
      • (18) Washers
      • (2) O rings (allows you to adjust the tension)
      • (1) Titanium key fob link

    Will my keys fit?

    Use the following dimensions to find out:
      • Length of the KeyBar - 3.5"
      • Width of each rounded end - .95"
      • Distance between screw holes - 2.55"
      • Screw post diameter - .164"

How much does the KeyBar weigh?

      • Less than 2 ounces
      • Less than 4 house keys

    What can I put in the KeyBar?

      • Up to 12 keys and inserts with included screws
      • Up to 28 keys and inserts with extension screws

column9: The enhanced deep carry comes in titanium and can fit any KeyBar that features the cutout slot for our regular clip. The clip will not work with KeyBars that have milled clips that screw onto the KeyBar. The clip features a thicker body, providing more durability and stability in your pocket.
column10:
We have designed an enhanced, deep carry clip to fit any KeyBar that features the cutout slot for our regular clip. The clip will not work with KeyBars that have milled clips that screw onto the KeyBar. These clips are made out of grade 5 titanium. Features of the enhanced design include a thicker and more durable structure. The clips also feature a smooth, surface finish.

The bottom end of the clip is a lot thicker to provide more stability in your pocket. When connecting the clip to the back plate of the KeyBar, we replaced the traditional circular cutout with a square cutout to allow the screw to connect easier for an easier assembly.

column5: Tool Insert Set: Mini Utility Tool & Phillips Screwdriver with Locking Plate
column9:
• For full size KeyBar
  • Made of Grade 5 6AL-4V Titanium .08" thick
  • Uses a Titanium KB Detent Lock, allowing the tool to snap into the open/closed position with just the right amount of resistance
  • Cam Lock uses torsion bars with stainless steel studs
  • Locks are stackable allowing you to add extra tools
  • The Full Size KeyBar takes TWO of the locking tools per lock
column10:
What's included?

      • (1) Titanium Mini Utility Tool Insert
      • (1) Titanium Phillips Screwdriver Tool Insert
      • (1) Set of 10 stainless steel mini razor blades
      • (1) Titanium KB Detent Lock, Full Size

This KeyBar tool insert bundle includes 2 of our most popular inserts! These solid titanium tools are for the full size KeyBar and function with the KB Detent Lock, which uses torsion bars with stainless steel studs that jump over cams machined on the tool inserts giving a satisfying SNAP when opened and closed with just the right amount of resistance.The locks are stackable allowing you to add extra tools. The Full Size KeyBar takes TWO of the new tools per lock ; the JR Size only uses ONE tool per lock.

The Mini Utility tool is made up of a titanium body and steel blade. Included are ten blades. The blade can be removed without having to disassemble your KeyBar.

Blade Installation Instructions:
To install the blade, open the tension plate all the way to expose the pocket.  Drop the razor blade into place, making sure it is flat in the pocket so that it is secure.  Close tension plate. Mini Utility Tool Insert is ready for use.

Disclaimer: The KeyBar Mini Utility Tool Insert is intended for use with your KeyBar product.  The Mini Utility Tool Insert is, of course, very sharp and could cause bodily injury if not handled carefully.  Users of the KeyBar Mini Utility Tool Insert should take special care to ensure that the blade insert itself is not left exposed when not in use, and that it is folded fully into the closed position.  Never use the Mini Utility Tool Insert while otherwise occupied or distracted, such as when operating a motor vehicle.  Users of the Mini Utility Tool Insert should also use extreme caution when using the Mini Utility Tool Insert, as there is the potential for bodily injury.   The Mini Utility Tool Insert is not a toy, and is likewise not intended to be used as a hunting, or similar knife, and will not withstand forces necessary to cut through thick or solid materials.  The Mini Utility Tool Insert is not a replacement for ordinary, or everyday knives, but is only intended for very light use.  KeyBar, LLC is not responsible for any injury caused by misuse of the Mini Utility Tool Insert or negligence on the part of its owner or user.

Made from solid titanium, the Phillips Screwdriver Tool Insert 2.0 is a lightweight and light duty Grade 5 titanium #2 phillips head screwdriver that locks in the open and closed position thanks to our new titanium KB Detent Lock system.

column5: KeyBar JR Locking Tool Insert - You Choose
column9:
• For KeyBar JR models only (will not work with full size KeyBar models)
  • Uses a Titanium KB Detent Lock, allowing the tool to snap into the open/closed position with just the right amount of resistance
  • Locks are stackable allowing you to add extra tools
  • Tool and lock are two separate items so depending on the number of keys and other tools being added you may need JR Extension Screws
  • Chisel cannot be colored
column10:
Choose the locking tool insert you want for your KeyBar JR! These solid titanium tools function with the JR KB Detent Lock, which uses torsion bars with stainless steel studs that jump over cams machined on the tool inserts giving a satisfying SNAP when opened and closed with just the right amount of resistance. The locks are stackable allowing you to add extra tools. The JR Size only uses ONE tool per lock, whereas the Full Size KeyBar takes TWO of the new tools per lock.

The Bottle Bomber 2.0 insert for KeyBar is a bottle opener specially designed for the KeyBar. Bottle opener features a quick access tab, flathead screwdriver, and a pry tool and that locks in the open and closed position thanks to our new titanium KB Detent Lock system.


The Flathead Screwdriver Tool Insert 2.0 is a lightweight and light duty Grade 5 titanium #2 flat head screwdriver that locks in the open and closed position thanks to our new titanium KB Detent Lock system. Can also function as a pry tool.


The Phillips Screwdriver Tool Insert 2.0 is a lightweight and light duty Grade 5 titanium #2 phillips head screwdriver that locks in the open and closed position thanks to our new titanium KB Detent Lock system.


The Mini Utility tool is made up of a titanium body and steel blade that locks in the open and closed position thanks to our new titanium KB Detent Lock system. Included are ten blades. The blade can be removed without having to disassemble your KeyBar.

The Chisel is a more permanent version of the Mini Utility Tool, in that there is no removable blade. It is made of S90V Stainless Steel and is a limited edition.


Blade Installation Instructions:
To install the blade, open the tension plate all the way to expose the pocket.  Drop the razor blade into place, making sure it is flat in the pocket so that it is secure.  Close tension plate. Mini Utility Tool Insert is ready for use.

column9: The enhanced deep carry comes in titanium and can fit any KeyBar that features the cutout slot for our regular clip. The clip will not work with KeyBars that have milled clips that screw onto the KeyBar. The clip features a thicker body, providing more durability and stability in your pocket.
column10:
We have designed an enhanced, deep carry clip to fit any KeyBar that features the cutout slot for our regular clip. The clip will not work with KeyBars that have milled clips that screw onto the KeyBar. These clips are made out of grade 5 titanium and are cut in-house with our water jet. Features of the enhanced design include a thicker and more durable structure. The clips also feature a smooth, surface finish.

The bottom end of the clip is a lot thicker to provide more stability in your pocket. When connecting the clip to the back plate of the KeyBar, we replaced the traditional circular cutout with a square cutout to allow the screw to connect easier for an easier assembly.

column5: Full Size KeyBar Locking Tool Insert Set - You Choose
column9:
• For full size KeyBar
  • Made of Grade 5 6AL-4V Titanium .08" thick
  • Uses a Titanium KB Detent Lock, allowing the tool to snap into the open/closed position with just the right amount of resistance
  • Cam Lock uses torsion bars with stainless steel studs
  • Locks are stackable allowing you to add extra tools
  • The Full Size KeyBar takes TWO of the locking tools per lock
  • Chisel cannot be colored
column10:
What's included?

      • (2) Titanium Tool Inserts of Your Choice
      • (1) Titanium KB Detent Lock, Full Size

This KeyBar tool insert bundle lets you choose the two locking tool inserts you want for your full size KeyBar! These solid titanium tools are for the full size KeyBar and function with the KB Detent Lock, which uses torsion bars with stainless steel studs that jump over cams machined on the tool inserts giving a satisfying SNAP when opened and closed with just the right amount of resistance. The locks are stackable allowing you to add extra tools. The Full Size KeyBar takes TWO of the new tools per lock ; the JR Size only uses ONE tool per lock.

The Bottle Bomber 2.0 insert for KeyBar is a bottle opener specially designed for the KeyBar. Bottle opener features a quick access tab, flathead screwdriver, and a pry tool and that locks in the open and closed position thanks to our new titanium KB Detent Lock system.


The Flathead Screwdriver Tool Insert 2.0 is a lightweight and light duty Grade 5 titanium #2 flat head screwdriver that locks in the open and closed position thanks to our new titanium KB Detent Lock system. Can also function as a pry tool.


The Phillips Screwdriver Tool Insert 2.0 is a lightweight and light duty Grade 5 titanium #2 phillips head screwdriver that locks in the open and closed position thanks to our new titanium KB Detent Lock system.


The Mini Utility tool is made up of a titanium body and steel blade that locks in the open and closed position thanks to our new titanium KB Detent Lock system. Included are ten blades. The blade can be removed without having to disassemble your KeyBar.

The Chisel is a more permanent version of the Mini Utility Tool, in that there is no removable blade. It is made of S90V Stainless Steel and is a limited edition.


Blade Installation Instructions:
To install the blade, open the tension plate all the way to expose the pocket.  Drop the razor blade into place, making sure it is flat in the pocket so that it is secure.  Close tension plate. Mini Utility Tool Insert is ready for use.


Disclaimer:

The KeyBar Mini Utility Tool Insert is intended for use with your KeyBar product.  The Mini Utility Tool Insert is, of course, very sharp and could cause bodily injury if not handled carefully.  Users of the KeyBar Mini Utility Tool Insert should take special care to ensure that the blade insert itself is not left exposed when not in use, and that it is folded fully into the closed position.  Never use the Mini Utility Tool Insert while otherwise occupied or distracted, such as when operating a motor vehicle.  Users of the Mini Utility Tool Insert should also use extreme caution when using the Mini Utility Tool Insert, as there is the potential for bodily injury.   The Mini Utility Tool Insert is not a toy, and is likewise not intended to be used as a hunting, or similar knife, and will not withstand forces necessary to cut through thick or solid materials.  The Mini Utility Tool Insert is not a replacement for ordinary, or everyday knives, but is only intended for very light use.  KeyBar, LLC is not responsible for any injury caused by misuse of the Mini Utility Tool Insert or negligence on the part of its owner or user.

The KeyBar Chisel Tool Insert is intended for use with your KeyBar product.  The Chisel Tool Insert is, of course, very sharp and could cause bodily injury if not handled carefully.  Users of the KeyBar Chisel Tool Insert should take special care to ensure that the blade insert itself is not left exposed when not in use, and that it is folded fully into the closed position.  Never use the Chisel Tool Insert while otherwise occupied or distracted, such as when operating a motor vehicle.  Users of the Chisel Tool Insert should also use extreme caution when using the Chisel Tool Insert, as there is the potential for bodily injury.

The Chisel Tool Insert is not a toy, and is likewise not intended to be used as a hunting, or similar knife, and will not withstand forces necessary to cut through thick or solid materials.  The Chisel Tool Insert is not a replacement for ordinary, or everyday knives, but is only intended for very light use.  KeyBar, LLC is not responsible for any injury caused by misuse of the Chisel Tool Insert or negligence on the part of its owner or user.

column10:
We have redesigned the titanium deep carry pocket clip to feature a rounded tip and deeper chamfer. The deep carry clip 3.0 will fit any KeyBar that features the cutout slot for our regular clip. The clip will not work with KeyBars that have milled clips that screw onto the KeyBar or the KeyBar JR. 

The bottom end of the clip is thicker to provide more stability in your pocket. When connecting the clip to the back plate of the KeyBar, we replaced the circular cutout from the standard pocket clip with a square cutout to allow the screw to connect easier for an easier assembly.

KeyBar's Quick Draw revolving desk organizer helps you show off/organize your desk tools in style. Can be used as a pen holder, tool holder, art supplies holder, etc.

Together this makes the Quick Draw an amazing desk organization display, conversation piece, and fidget-spinner for those moments at your desk that you just need to spin some more ideas into your thought process.

The laser polished blade features an opening tab and thumb notch to deploy the blade. The Tanto Blade Insert is constructed out of MagnaCut Steel made by Mike Taylor.

Instructions for assembly are included on the back of the tin. Included are a set of the new custom designed KeyBar screws.

Get organized and Stop the Noise with our classic Stonewashed Aluminum KeyBar JR. Made of high-end aircraft-grade aluminum, and stonewashed for that rugged classic look. It's a minimal yet sophisticated everyday carry sure to help you keep your essentials together in one perfect pocket sized package that can withstand some of the harshest environments. We've paired it with our most popular addition: the Small Aluminum MagNut.

The aluminum MagNut is a magnetic quick release specifically designed for the KeyBar to allow quick and easy connection for larger items, like your key fob, to your KeyBar. With a pull force of 6 1/2 lbs., items attached to your KeyBar with the MagNut are secure.

What's included?

    • (1) Stonewashed Aluminum KeyBar JR (Blister Packaged)
    • (1) Small Aluminum MagNut Quick Release Set

    Specs

    • Length of the KeyBar - 3.0625"
    • Width of rounded end - .95"
    • Distance between screw holes - 2.25"
    • Screw post diameter - .164"

Additional Information

  • The small MagNut set includes two MagNuts (a right and a left MagNut) each with a 1/2" diameter split ring and is pressed with 1/4" x 1/4" rare-earth (Neodymium Iron Boron in Grade N52) magnetic cylinder insert, which has a pull force of 6 1/2 lbs. Note: These rare-earth magnets will lose their magnetic properties if heated above 175 degrees Fahrenheit (80 degrees Celcius). The strong magnetic fields of these rare-earth magnets can damage items such as television, computer monitors, credit cards, bank cards, computers, data carriers, video tapes, mechanical watches, hearing aids and loud speakers. Pace-makers may be damaged or switch to "Test-Mode" in the presence of a strong magnetic force, if a pace-maker or other bodily implant is in use, keep a minimum of 3 feet distance. Keep away from small children. Under no circumstances should you try to cut, saw or drill the rare earth magnet as the resulting dust is very flammable.  You should also not burn the magnet as it will create toxic fumes.

Get organized and Stop the Noise with our classic Stonewash Aluminum KeyBar. Made of high-end aircraft-grade aluminum, and stonewashed for that rugged classic look. It's a simple yet sophisticated everyday carry sure to gain attention. Keep your essentials together in one perfect pocket sized package that can withstand some of the harshest environments.

The aluminum MagNut is a magnetic quick release specifically designed for the KeyBar to allow quick and easy connection for larger items, like your key fob, to your KeyBar. With a pull force of 6 1/2 lbs., items attached to your KeyBar with the MagNut are secure. Included in this deal is a set of titanium split rings which are non-magnetic so that the magnets don't make the MagNuts stick to the split rings!

The titanium pick specially designed for the KeyBar. Perfect for detailed pick work, eating, punching leather, you name it. The titanium Tweezers specially designed for the KeyBar. Designed to perfectly nest along with your keys and designed sturdy and precise to hold up to years of use.

Trying to simplify your KeyBar to it's max potential? The Titanium Multi-Tool Insert is KeyBar's all-in-one insert for KeyBar and KeyBar JRs. This insert has so many functionalities, its insane to think about just how we managed to fit them all into such a small package. The tool has a chamfered end to be used as a prybar, followed by a bottle opener cut out and a ridge indented finger rest for added torque when using the aforementioned functions. That ridge line also doubles as a cap-grip opener when seated and closed into the KeyBar. On the flip side there's a laser engraved ruler with 1/16" increments for those times you need to take small measurements without having to whip out a flimsy tape measurer. Even more?? The thumbstud switch also acts as a small nail file, and yet again, KeyBar logo side has the same cuts to be utilized as a forever-strike!

Disclaimer:

The KeyBar Chisel Tool Insert is intended for use with your KeyBar product.  The Chisel Tool Insert is, of course, very sharp and could cause bodily injury if not handled carefully.  Users of the KeyBar Chisel Tool Insert should take special care to ensure that the blade insert itself is not left exposed when not in use, and that it is folded fully into the closed position.  Never use the Chisel Tool Insert while otherwise occupied or distracted, such as when operating a motor vehicle.  Users of the Chisel Tool Insert should also use extreme caution when using the Chisel Tool Insert, as there is the potential for bodily injury.

The Chisel Tool Insert is not a toy, and is likewise not intended to be used as a hunting, or similar knife, and will not withstand forces necessary to cut through thick or solid materials.  The Chisel Tool Insert is not a replacement for ordinary, or everyday knives, but is only intended for very light use.  KeyBar, LLC is not responsible for any injury caused by misuse of the Chisel Tool Insert or negligence on the part of its owner or user.

Grab this Blacked Out Bundle and save BIG! So many of you love all black EDC items, so we've paired our Black G10 KeyBar with black cerakoted stainless steel screws, blackwashed titanium 3.0 deep carry clip, and black anodized MagNuts! This setup looks so sleek and strong.

The aluminum MagNut is a magnetic quick release specifically designed for the KeyBar to allow quick and easy connection for larger items, like your key fob, to your KeyBar. With a pull force of 6 1/2 lbs., items attached to your KeyBar with the MagNut are secure.

What's included?

    • (1) Black G10 KeyBar (Full Size)
    • (1) Set of Black Cerakoted SS Screws (1/2", 3/4" and 7/8")

    • Width of rounded end - .95"
    • Distance between screw holes - 2.25"
    • Screw post diameter - .164"

Additional Information

  • The small MagNut set includes two MagNuts (a right and a left MagNut) each with a 1/2" diameter split ring and is pressed with 1/4" x 1/4" rare-earth (Neodymium Iron Boron in Grade N52) magnetic cylinder insert, which has a pull force of 6 1/2 lbs. Note: These rare-earth magnets will lose their magnetic properties if heated above 175 degrees Fahrenheit (80 degrees Celcius). The strong magnetic fields of these rare-earth magnets can damage items such as television, computer monitors, credit cards, bank cards, computers, data carriers, video tapes, mechanical watches, hearing aids and loud speakers. Pace-makers may be damaged or switch to "Test-Mode" in the presence of a strong magnetic force, if a pace-maker or other bodily implant is in use, keep a minimum of 3 feet distance. Keep away from small children. Under no circumstances should you try to cut, saw or drill the rare earth magnet as the resulting dust is very flammable.  You should also not burn the magnet as it will create toxic fumes.

Get organized and “Stop the Noise” with our classic Stonewashed Titanium KeyBar. Made of high-end titanium, and stonewashed for that rugged classic look. It’s a simple yet sophisticated everyday carry sure to gain attention. Keep your essentials together in one perfect pocket sized package that can withstand some of the harshest environments.

The aluminum MagNut is a magnetic quick release specifically designed for the KeyBar to allow quick and easy connection for larger items, like your key fob, to your KeyBar. With a pull force of 6 1/2 lbs., items attached to your KeyBar with the MagNut are secure. Included in this deal is a set of titanium split rings which are non-magnetic so that the magnets don't make the MagNuts stick to the split rings!

This KeyBar tool insert bundle includes 2 of our most popular inserts! These solid titanium tools are for the full size KeyBar and function with the KB Detent Lock, which uses torsion bars with stainless steel studs that jump over cams machined on the tool inserts giving a satisfying SNAP when opened and closed with just the right amount of resistance.The locks are stackable allowing you to add extra tools. The Full Size KeyBar takes TWO of the new tools per lock ; the JR Size only uses ONE tool per lock.

The Mini Utility tool is made up of a titanium body and steel blade. Included are ten blades. The blade can be removed without having to disassemble your KeyBar.

Made from solid titanium, the Phillips Screwdriver Tool Insert 2.0 is a lightweight and light duty Grade 5 titanium #2 phillips head screwdriver that locks in the open and closed position thanks to our new titanium KB Detent Lock system.

Blade Installation Instructions:
To install the blade, open the tension plate all the way to expose the pocket.  Drop the razor blade into place, making sure it is flat in the pocket so that it is secure.  Close tension plate. Mini Utility Tool Insert is ready for use.

Disclaimer: The KeyBar Mini Utility Tool Insert is intended for use with your KeyBar product.  The Mini Utility Tool Insert is, of course, very sharp and could cause bodily injury if not handled carefully.  Users of the KeyBar Mini Utility Tool Insert should take special care to ensure that the blade insert itself is not left exposed when not in use, and that it is folded fully into the closed position.  Never use the Mini Utility Tool Insert while otherwise occupied or distracted, such as when operating a motor vehicle.  Users of the Mini Utility Tool Insert should also use extreme caution when using the Mini Utility Tool Insert, as there is the potential for bodily injury.   The Mini Utility Tool Insert is not a toy, and is likewise not intended to be used as a hunting, or similar knife, and will not withstand forces necessary to cut through thick or solid materials.  The Mini Utility Tool Insert is not a replacement for ordinary, or everyday knives, but is only intended for very light use.  KeyBar, LLC is not responsible for any injury caused by misuse of the Mini Utility Tool Insert or negligence on the part of its owner or user.

What's included?

    • (1) Stonewashed Titanium KeyBar (Full Size) with deep carry 3.0 titanium pocket clip
    • (1) Small Aluminum MagNut Quick Release Set
    • (1) Full Size Tool Lock
    • (1) Titanium Phillips Screwdriver
    • (1) Titanium/SS Mini Utility Tool (MUT)

    Specs

    • Length of the KeyBar - 3.0625"
    • Width of rounded end - .95"
    • Distance between screw holes - 2.25"
    • Screw post diameter - .164"

  • The small MagNut set includes two MagNuts (a right and a left MagNut) each with a 1/2" diameter split ring and is pressed with 1/4" x 1/4" rare-earth (Neodymium Iron Boron in Grade N52) magnetic cylinder insert, which has a pull force of 6 1/2 lbs. Note: These rare-earth magnets will lose their magnetic properties if heated above 175 degrees Fahrenheit (80 degrees Celcius). The strong magnetic fields of these rare-earth magnets can damage items such as television, computer monitors, credit cards, bank cards, computers, data carriers, video tapes, mechanical watches, hearing aids and loud speakers. The Tanto insert expands the multitool functionality of the standard KeyBar. The Tanto securely locks in the open and has a detent holding it in the closed position with the included 6-Al-4V titanium Drop-Lock plate. The blade features a flat, zero grind on the tip and is available in two finishes, laser polished and laser polished multicolor crystalized. The Tanto Blade Insert is constructed out of S90V Steel made by Mike Taylor and has an opening tab and thumb notch to deploy the blade.

Instructions for assembly are included on the back of the tin. Assembly instructions indicate that brass washers are included; that is incorrect and should be SS washers, which are included.

column9:
• Includes:
    • Small Aluminum MagNuts
    • Titanium Pick Insert
    • Titanium Tweezers Insert
    • Titanium Multi-Tool Insert
column10:
The aluminum MagNut is a magnetic quick release specifically designed for the KeyBar to allow quick and easy connection for larger items, like your key fob, to your KeyBar. With a pull force of 6 1/2 lbs., items attached to your KeyBar with the MagNut are secure. Included in this deal is a set of titanium split rings which are non-magnetic so that the magnets don't make the MagNuts stick to the split rings!

The titanium pick specially designed for the KeyBar. Perfect for detailed pick work, eating, punching leather, you name it. The titanium Tweezers specially designed for the KeyBar. Designed to perfectly nest along with your keys and designed sturdy and precise to hold up to years of use.

Trying to simplify your KeyBar to it's max potential? The Titanium Multi-Tool Insert is KeyBar's all-in-one insert for KeyBar and KeyBar JRs. This insert has so many functionalities, its insane to think about just how we managed to fit them all into such a small package. The tool has a chamfered end to be used as a prybar, followed by a bottle opener cut out and a ridge indented finger rest for added torque when using the aforementioned functions. That ridge line also doubles as a cap-grip opener when seated and closed into the KeyBar. On the flip side there's a laser engraved ruler with 1/16" increments for those times you need to take small measurements without having to whip out a flimsy tape measurer. Even more?? The thumbstud switch also acts as a small nail file, and yet again, KeyBar logo side has the same cuts to be utilized as a forever-strike!

What's included?

    • (1) Small Aluminum MagNut Quick Release Set
    • (1) Titanium Pick
    • (1) Titanium Tweezers
    • (1) Titanium Multi-Tool

    Specs

    • Length of the KeyBar - 3.0625"
    • Width of rounded end - .95"
    • Distance between screw holes - 2.25"
    • Screw post diameter - .164"

Additional Information

  • The small MagNut set includes two MagNuts (a right and a left MagNut) each with a 1/2" diameter split ring and is pressed with 1/4" x 1/4" rare-earth (Neodymium Iron Boron in Grade N52) magnetic cylinder insert, which has a pull force of 6 1/2 lbs. Note: These rare-earth magnets will lose their magnetic properties if heated above 175 degrees Fahrenheit (80 degrees Celcius). The strong magnetic fields of these rare-earth magnets can damage items such as television, computer monitors, credit cards, bank cards, computers, data carriers, video tapes, mechanical watches, hearing aids and loud speakers. Pace-makers may be damaged or switch to "Test-Mode" in the presence of a strong magnetic force, if a pace-maker or other bodily implant is in use, keep a minimum of 3 feet distance. Keep away from small children. Under no circumstances should you try to cut, saw or drill the rare earth magnet as the resulting dust is very flammable.  You should also not burn the magnet as it will create toxic fumes.

The titanium pick specially designed for the KeyBar. Perfect for detailed pick work, eating, punching leather, you name it.

These solid titanium tools are for the full size KeyBar and function with the KB Detent Lock, which uses torsion bars with stainless steel studs that jump over cams machined on the tool inserts giving a satisfying SNAP when opened and closed with just the right amount of resistance.The locks are stackable allowing you to add extra tools. The Full Size KeyBar takes TWO of the new tools per lock ; the JR Size only uses ONE tool per lock.

The Mini Utility tool is made up of a titanium body and steel blade. Included are ten blades. The blade can be removed without having to disassemble your KeyBar.

Made from solid titanium, the Phillips Screwdriver Tool Insert 2.0 is a lightweight and light duty Grade 5 titanium #2 phillips head screwdriver that locks in the open and closed position thanks to our new titanium KB Detent Lock system.

Blade Installation Instructions:
To install the blade, open the tension plate all the way to expose the pocket.  Drop the razor blade into place, making sure it is flat in the pocket so that it is secure.  Close tension plate. Mini Utility Tool Insert is ready for use.

Disclaimer: The KeyBar Mini Utility Tool Insert is intended for use with your KeyBar product.  The Mini Utility Tool Insert is, of course, very sharp and could cause bodily injury if not handled carefully.  Users of the KeyBar Mini Utility Tool Insert should take special care to ensure that the blade insert itself is not left exposed when not in use, and that it is folded fully into the closed position.  Never use the Mini Utility Tool Insert while otherwise occupied or distracted, such as when operating a motor vehicle.  Users of the Mini Utility Tool Insert should also use extreme caution when using the Mini Utility Tool Insert, as there is the potential for bodily injury.   The Mini Utility Tool Insert is not a toy, and is likewise not intended to be used as a hunting, or similar knife, and will not withstand forces necessary to cut through thick or solid materials.  The Mini Utility Tool Insert is not a replacement for ordinary, or everyday knives, but is only intended for very light use.  KeyBar, LLC is not responsible for any injury caused by misuse of the Mini Utility Tool Insert or negligence on the part of its owner or user.

column9: Pick one up from our dealer PVK: Hawk Titanium KeyBar!
column10:
The Hawk Titanium KeyBar featuring the Hawk Knife Designs Grip Clip is a collab with legendary designer Gavin Hawk. This KeyBar is the premium EDC solution engineered for those who demand rugged reliability and refined design in one sleek package.

The KeyBar is a minimalist key organizer that tames noisy, bulky keychains with precision. It holds up to 12 standard keys or tools with the included screws, keeping them compact, quiet, and easily accessible. Extension screws for more keys and tools are available for purchase. Produced in the USA from titanium, this KeyBar is durable and features a stonewashed finish.

The Hawk Knife Designs Titanium Grip Clip, designed by the maker of some of the most innovative knives in the industry, is strong, functional, and subtly aggressive—perfect for EDC enthusiasts who appreciate gear that works as hard as they do.

This limited edition run will sell out fast!

What's included?

    • (1) Branded hinged tin
    • (1) Custom Titanium Hawk Knife Designs Logo KeyBar with Hawk Knife Designs Titanium Grip Clip
    • (2) Stainless steel 1/2" screws (up to 4 keys)
    • (2) Stainless steel 3/4" screws (up to 8 keys)
    • (2) Stainless steel 7/8" screws (up to 12 keys)
    • (18) Washers
    • (2) O rings (allows you to adjust the tension)
    • (1) Titanium key fob link

    Will my keys fit?

    Use the following dimensions to find out:

    • Length of the KeyBar - 3.5"
    • Width of each rounded end - .95"
    • Distance between screw holes - 2.55"
    • Screw post diameter - .164"

How much does the KeyBar weigh?

    • Less than 2 ounces
    • Less than 4 house keys

    What can I put in the KeyBar?

    • Up to 12 keys and inserts with included screws
    • Up to 28 keys and inserts with extension screws

column9:
• S30VN Steel Tanto Model
  • Flat, zero grind on the tip
  • Laser Polished Grade
  • Total cutting length: 2"
  • Made by M. Taylor
  • Secure locking with titanium drop-lock
  • Fits FULL SIZE KeyBar models; does not fit JR KeyBar models
  • Discounts do not apply
column10:
The Tanto insert expands the multitool functionality of the standard KeyBar. The Tanto securely locks in the open and has a detent holding it in the closed position with the included 6-Al-4V titanium Drop-Lock plate. The blade features a flat, zero grind on the tip and is available in two finishes, laser polished and laser polished multicolor crystalized. The Tanto Blade Insert is constructed out of S30VN Steel made by Mike Taylor and has an opening tab and thumb notch to deploy the blade.

Instructions for assembly are included on the back of the tin. Assembly instructions indicate that brass washers are included; that is incorrect and should be SS washers, which are included.

What's included?

  • (1) Branded hinged tin
  • (1) S30VN Steel Tanto Insert
  • (1) Drop-Lock Detent
  • (2) Stand-off Washer
  • (2) SS Blade Washers
  • (1) Tip Protector
