column5: Doc Shiffer S30V Recon Blade Insert
column9:
• Recon Style Blade
  • Hand ground by the legendary Doc Shiffer
  • S30V Stainless Steel blade
  • . 125 inch thick, 2 inch long blade 
  • Titanium Drop-Lock detent plate
  • Fits Full-Size KeyBars only
column10:
Here's what Doc has to say about this blade style: "The Recon is my first standard folder model. It came about from a request from members of the Force Recon unit I was a member of. They wanted a new knife for the E&E survival kit. I took the initial design we came up with and after several prototypes we had the Recon. The current style is version 3. This model originated in 2009."

Doc redesigned the blade so it would fit in a KeyBar for us! Don't miss out on this limited edition run.

What's included?

    • (1) Limited Edition Doc Shiffer/KeyBar tin
    • (1) Limited Edition Doc Shiffer/KeyBar S30V Recon blade insert
    • (1) Titanium KeyBar Drop Lock Insert
    • (1) 3D Printed Back Spacer
    • (2) SS Washers

    Specs

    • Weight: Less than 1 ounce
    • Cutting length: 2"
    • Actual dimensions: 3” x 1” .125”

column9:

column10:
This bundle includes a Custom Microfiber Cloth and your choice of the Mini Driver/MagNut Tool or the Screw Blaster.

The microfiber cloth is great for cleaning, protecting and using as a place to keep your KeyBar and other gear. Produced in the USA by Rick Bloomer of Dragon Cut Design, this cloth measures 5.25″ x 7.25″ and is gray on the cloth side and white on the microfiber side.

The mini screwdriver tool features an Aluminum MagNut with a Titanium Split Ring at the top so it can be attached to a convenient location and easily retrieved when needed. The bit socket features a magnetic end to secure the included screwdriver bit. The Mini Driver/MagNut tool measures 1.5" long.

The Rotating Screw Blaster features a magnetic socket to secure the included screwdriver bit and is 2.625" long. The ceramic bearing at the top allows easier use when twisting left or right. The bit choices offered are Phillips or Flathead and are 1" (25.4mm) long with a 1/4" (6.35mm) hex shank and quick release slot.

What's included?

      • (1) Microfiber Cloth
      • (1) Mini Driver/MagNut Tool OR Screw Blaster

column10:
The Small MagNut set is a magnetic quick clasp specifically designed for the KeyBar but works on tools or other pesky items for which you need a quick mounting solution.

A set includes two MagNuts (a right and a left MagNut) each with a 1/2" titanium split ring.

MagNuts come in a choice of small aluminu MagNuts with pressed 1/4" x 1/4" rare-earth (Neodymium Iron Boron in Grade N52) magnetic cylinder insert, which has a pull force of 6 1/2 lbs.

Note: These rare-earth magnets will lose their magnetic properties if heated above 175 degrees Fahrenheit (80 degrees Celcius). The strong magnetic fields of these rare-earth magnets can damage items such as television, computer monitors, credit cards, bank cards, computers, data carriers, video tapes, mechanical watches, hearing aids and loud speakers. Pace-makers may be damaged or switch to "Test-Mode" in the presence of a strong magnetic force, if a pace-maker or other bodily implant is in use, keep a minimum of 3 feet distance. Keep away from small children. Under no circumstances should you try to cut, saw or drill the rare earth magnet as the resulting dust is very flammable.  You should also not burn the magnet as it will create toxic fumes.

column10:
Get organized and Stop the Noise with our classic Stonewashed Aluminum KeyBar JR. Made of high-end aircraft-grade aluminum, and stonewashed for that rugged classic look. It's a minimal yet sophisticated everyday carry sure to help you keep your essentials together in one perfect pocket sized package that can withstand some of the harshest environments. We've paired it with our S30V Mini Chisel Tool Insert, the next level version of the Mini Utility Tool Insert.

Disclaimer:

The KeyBar Chisel Tool Insert is intended for use with your KeyBar product.  The Chisel Tool Insert is, of course, very sharp and could cause bodily injury if not handled carefully.  Users of the KeyBar Chisel Tool Insert should take special care to ensure that the blade insert itself is not left exposed when not in use, and that it is folded fully into the closed position.  Never use the Chisel Tool Insert while otherwise occupied or distracted, such as when operating a motor vehicle.  Users of the Chisel Tool Insert should also use extreme caution when using the Chisel Tool Insert, as there is the potential for bodily injury.

The Chisel Tool Insert is not a toy, and is likewise not intended to be used as a hunting, or similar knife, and will not withstand forces necessary to cut through thick or solid materials.  The Chisel Tool Insert is not a replacement for ordinary, or everyday knives, but is only intended for very light use.  KeyBar, LLC is not responsible for any injury caused by misuse of the Chisel Tool Insert or negligence on the part of its owner or user.

What's included?
